;a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"amandablum";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2559:"<p>The team at <a title="WP e-Commerce Plugin Theme Partners" href="http://www.getshopped.org">WP e-Commerce</a> is proud to announce a new partnership with <a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a>. We love the team at iThemes personally, but the reason we really admire them is their ability to make WordPress easy: themes that just do what you ask, <a href="http://ithemes.com/find/plugins/">plugins</a> that don&#8217;t demand you be a developer. (You may notice we recommend <a href="http://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/">Backup Buddy</a> for your site backups whenever WPEC is upgraded).</p>\n<p>In particular, we love iThemes themes for WP e-Commerce. they&#8217;re easy to use and turn WP e-Commerce into a slick, clean, customizable shop in a flash. You&#8217;ll notice you can now purchase <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/">premium themes</a> in addition to plugins. We&#8217;re launching with two themes: <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/depot-theme-for-wp-e-commerce-by-ithemes/">Depot</a> and <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/market-theme-for-wp-e-commerce-by-ithemes/">Market</a>.<br />\n<a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/depot-shopp-400x290.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-297678" title="depot-shopp-400x290" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/depot-shopp-400x290.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="290" /></a><a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/market-400x290.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-297675" title="market-400x290" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/market-400x290.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="290" /></a></p>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<p>Both feature multiple page templates, a beautiful design that pushes products to the forefront. Depot is a clean theme with a focus on marketing, ideal for clothes or retail or anything you can dream up. Market is a sleek and smart theme that allows Grid View to really shine, while allowing customers to visualize products in a sensible way.</p>\n<p>The team at WP e-Commerce is working hard to bring new add ons to you, including a wealth of theming options in the new year. We&#8217;re thrilled to launch with a partner as experienced as iThemes.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/">WP e-Commerce Proud to Partner with iThemes</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:56:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:97:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:106:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 12 Dec 2012 17:25:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"GetShopped News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"3.8.9.4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"blank checkout";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"media manager";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"shipwire";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=297037";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:604:"<p>WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now available for download. In this release, we fixed some major issues with certain hosting configurations, especially the dreaded blank checkout page, or error when adding items to cart. We also made sure WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is playing nice with WordPress 3.5. You will notice that the product edit page is [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3046:"<p>WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now available for download.</p>\n<p>In this release, we fixed some major issues with certain hosting configurations, especially the dreaded blank checkout page, or error when adding items to cart. We also made sure WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is playing nice with WordPress 3.5. You will notice that the product edit page is properly supporting the new media UI introduced in WordPress 3.5. It certainly makes managing product images much more pleasant.</p>\n<p>Below you can find the list of changes made in this release:</p>\n<pre>* Fix: "No shipping quotes" error is displayed when selecting\r\n"Shipping same as billing".\r\n* Fix: Avoid flooding transient data when site''s feed is being\r\n  visited by bots.\r\n* Fix: Blank Checkout page for some certain installation when\r\n  Shipping is enabled.\r\n* Fix: Can''t add to cart on some server.\r\n* Fix: Fatal error when viewing product variation iframe, because\r\n  _wp_admin_html_begin() does not exist on older WordPress versions.\r\n* Fix: MySQL error/warning in _wpsc_filter_special_widget_where().\r\n* Fix: Only show attachment fields when viewed on an edit product page.\r\n* Fix: PHP Notice in cart.class.php.\r\n* Fix: Properly escape columns in admin products page.\r\n* Fix: Purchase log''s item names are not translatable via qTranslate.\r\n* Fix: Shipping same as billing saves "State" field label as the\r\n  shipping region.\r\n* Fix: Shipwire settings are not updated.\r\n* Fix: Shipwire syncing doesn''t take into consideration products in\r\n  trash, or multiple products using the same SKUs (as in WPML)\r\n* Fix: Specials widget is empty when there are no product with variation\r\n  sales.\r\n* Fix: Variation sets are not being sorted on the front-end.\r\n* Fix: WPEC doesn''t cooperate with WP 3.5 media UI.\r\n* Fix: wpsc_pre_transaction_results filter is ignored.\r\n* Make sure admin styles are enqueued for product variations iframe in\r\n  older version of WordPress.</pre>\n<p>It is extremely important that before you upgrade to 3.8.9.4, <strong>please back up your files and databases</strong>. <a href="http://ithemes.com/member/go.php?r=27731&amp;i=l44">Backup Buddy</a> is our top choice for making backup simple and effortless.</p>\n<h5>How to upgrade</h5>\n<p>You can simply use WordPress automatic updates feature to download and install WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4.</p>\n<p>If that doesn&#8217;t work for you, try the following steps for a manual upgrade:</p>\n<p>- <a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.9.4.zip">Download WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 from here</a> and save it to your computer.</p>\n<p>- Extract the downloaded package to a folder on your computer.</p>\n<p>- Upload the contents of that folder to this path on your server, overwriting all existing files: <code>wp-content/plugins/wp-e-commerce</code></p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:102:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"56";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:50:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"WP Affiliate Manager 1.4.x Conflict with WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-affiliate-manager-1-4-x-conflict-with-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:110:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-affiliate-manager-1-4-x-conflict-with-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 09 Dec 2012 18:43:18 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"GetShopped News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Premium Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Affiliate Manager";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=296608";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:618:"<p>edit: 12/27/12: Affiliate Manager is fixed and back online We&#8217;ve been working with our friends at 9Seeds on some bug reports regarding Affiliate Manager. &#8220;There is a problem with WP Affiliate Manager 1.4.x and earlier and WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x. We have determined what the issue and are currently working on a fix. The issue only [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-affiliate-manager-1-4-x-conflict-with-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/">WP Affiliate Manager 1.4.x Conflict with WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"amandablum";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2107:"<p><strong>edit: 12/27/12: Affiliate Manager is fixed and back online</strong></p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve been working with our friends at 9Seeds on some bug reports regarding <a href="http://wpaffiliatemanager.com/forum/technical-support/issue-with-wp-affiliate-manager-and-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/#p187">Affiliate Manager.</a></p>\n<p><em>&#8220;There is a problem with WP Affiliate Manager 1.4.x and earlier and WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x. We have determined what the issue and are currently working on a fix. The issue only presents itself on new installations, where you&#8217;re activating WP Affiliate Manager for the first time with WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x.</em></p>\n<p>People that have had WP e-Commerce 3.8.8.x (or earlier) and WP Affiliate Manager running together smoothly should not worry about the upgrade to WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x. The problem only occurs when WP Affiliate Manager is activated for the first time with WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x.</p>\n<p>If you have found this information before installing &amp; activating WP Affiliate Manager and WP e-Commerce for the first time, there is a workaround. Install and activate WP Affiliate Manager first, and then WP e-Commerce.</p>\n<p>We are currently working on version 1.5 to fix this, and expect that it will be released within the next two weeks. Since the bug renders WP Affiliate Manager in a state of partial installation, we&#8217;ve had to take extensive steps to make sure those existing partial installations will be repaired to full working order. Announcements regarding the release (and possible betas for those with partial installations) will be made here.&#8221;</p>\n<p>For our part here at WP e-Commerce and Getshopped, we&#8217;ve temporarily removed Affiliate Manager from the store while this issue is remedied. We&#8217;ll keep in touch here regarding updates.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-affiliate-manager-1-4-x-conflict-with-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/">WP Affiliate Manager 1.4.x Conflict with WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.x</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:106:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-affiliate-manager-1-4-x-conflict-with-wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-x/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s